h3. Issue Summary

When using Automation Web Request component, calling Rest API v3 Create Issue operation, it does't accept the smart value {{issue.description.asJsonString}} in the Custom Data Body, to set the Description field, v2 does.
h3. Steps to Reproduce
 # Create an automation
 # Add a Send Web Request Component
 # Set the request URL to https://<<site>>/rest/api/3/issue
 # Set Web Request body to Custom data
 # Set in the Custom Data, set the Description to:
 ** 
{code:java}
 "description":{{issue.description.asJsonString}}
{code}

h3. Expected Results

Issue created successfully with the proper Description.
h3. Actual Results

 
  Error response HTTP body:
{code:java}
{
   "errorMessages":[
      
   ],
   "errors":{
      "description":"Operation value must be an Atlassian Document (see the Atlassian Document Format)"
   }
}
{code}
Error publishing web request. Response HTTP status:
 400
h3. Workaround

Change the API version to 2 and it will work:

From https://<<site>>/rest/api/3/issue to https://<<site>>/rest/api/2/issue

Currently, when creating a variable in a Automation rule to store array values, it will store the values from the array in a single position:
{code}Variable name: var
{{issue.testeautomation.value}}{code}

When writing it into a field using:

{code}{
    "fields": {
             
         "testeautomation" : [{ "value" : "{{var}}"}]
      }
    
}

 {code}

This is the output:

{code}Log action
Log
values var: com espaco, semespaco

Edit issue
Error editing issues
SCRUM-43 (Option value 'com espaco, semespaco' is not valid (customfield_10205)){code}

(the values are stored in a single position and doesn't match the options available on the checbox field)
